<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   Independent Presidential Candidate Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Independent Presidential Candidate Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0705075794 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1730 GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0705075794 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Carlos Jeque, former vice president of the 
Mozambique United Front-Democratic Convergence Party [Fumo-PCD], 
has told SAVANA that he will enter the presidential elections 
race as an independent candidate. Jeque, 41, is a lawyer. He 
told SAVANA that his decision comes in the wake of advice given 
by political and business individuals, adding that the latter 
are, quote, worried about the absence of a civilian alternative 
in view of their (?disappointment) in Dr. Domingos Arouca, whom 
we all trusted until very recently, unquote. 
  President Chissano, Afnso Dhlakama, leader of the Mozambique 
National Resistance, and FUMO-PCD President Domingos Arouca have 
already announced that they will run for the presidency. 

</TEXT>

