  [Text] Johannesburg, al-Ma' [May] 9, JAMAHIRIYAH NEWS 
AGENCY -- The secretary of the general people's committee for 
foreign liaison and international cooperation and the 
accompanying delegation have arrived in Johannesburg to take 
part in the ceremonies which well be held tomorrow on the 
occasion of appointing the African freedom-fighter Nelson 
Mandela as president for South Africa. 
  It is known that Nelson Mandela had been awarded the 
al-Qathafi international human rights prize. 

