<H3> <TI>   PAC No. 2 Man Resigns Parliament Seat; Other Changes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PAC No. 2 Man Resigns Parliament Seat; Other Changes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0705171094 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1606 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0705171094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg May 7 SAPA -- Pan Africanist Congress 
[PAC] stalwart Philip Johnson Mlambo has resigned his position 
on the National Assembly, according to the final list of 
representatives released by the Independent Electoral Commission 
[IEC] on Saturday [7 May]. 
  Mr Mlambo was the PAC's number two on an initial National 
Assembly list released by the IEC. 
  Mr Ahmed Gora Ebrahim now moves into the number two position 
behind PAC President Clarence Makwetu. 
  PAC Secretary General Bennie Alexander is another change, 
moving out from number three for his organisation on the 
National Assembly to serve in the PWV [Pretoria, Witwatersrand, 
Vereeniging] regional parliament, according to the IEC. 
  Ms Patricia de Lille has been elevated to number three for 
the PAC on the National Assembly and Mr Richard Sizani to number 
four. 

</TEXT>

