<H3> <TI>   Chief of Staff Issues Warning Over Bakassi Peninsula </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chief of Staff Issues Warning Over Bakassi Peninsula </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0905172094 Libreville Africa No. 1 in French 1215 GMT 7 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0905172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Libreville Africa No. 1 </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Nigerian chief of general staff, Lieutenant 
General Oladipo Diya, yesterday issued a severe warning 
regarding the Bakassi Peninsula saying: No one should try to 
put our determination to the test. Our claim of sovereignty 
over the Bakassi Peninsula is based on law and justice, he added. 
  Yesterday, Cameroonian External Relations Minister Ferdinand 
Oyono described the situation on the Bakassi Peninsula as 
potentially explosive. Troops from both countries have been 
deployed on the peninsula. 

</TEXT>

