<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mali </F>
<H3> <TI>   Republican Guards, Police Trainees Clash </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Republican Guards, Police Trainees Clash </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB1105165594 Dakar PANA in French 1108 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB1105165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Dakar PANA </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bamako, 11 May (PANA) -- Deadly clashes occurred 
here last night between Republican Guards and students of the 
Bamako Police Academy. The clashes, which involved the use of 
teargas, automatic pistols, and machine guns, resulted in many 
casualties, so far undisclosed, among the fighters and their 
families. The fighting lasted more than three hours, according 
to witnesses. 
  Republican Guards and police trainees undergoing training 
live in two camps in Bamako separated by a common wall. Sources 
say that a Republican Guard, Boubou Sylla, who wanted to take a 
shortcut through the training center, was allegedly molested by 
some student policemen leading to violent reprisals by the 
Republican Guards, who live with their families in their camp. 
However, women and children living on the premises were said to 
have been evacuated in time by paratroopers, who came from their 
quarters 5 km away to separate the fighting groups. 

</TEXT>

