<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Nelson Mandela has announced that South Africa 
has applied for readmission to the Commonwealth after an absence 
of more than 30 years. Pretoria left the organization in 1961, 
following the criticism of its apartheid policies. Commonwealth 
Secretary General Chief Emeka Anyaoku said South Africa was 
expected to rejoin the organization within a few weeks. 

