<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Nigeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Reports 2 Soldiers Killed on Bakassi Peninsula </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Reports 2 Soldiers Killed on Bakassi Peninsula </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB1205220894 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 2100 GMT 
12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB1205220894 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Army has confirmed that Cameroon has again 
mounted an aggression on Nigeria on the Bakassi Peninsula. A 
statement by the director of army public relations said that 
while Nigeria had resorted to diplomatic, political, and 
judicial means to resolve the dispute over the peninsula, 
Cameroon had consistently displayed arrogant repression. This, 
it said, had resulted in the death of two Nigerian soldiers 
recently. 
  The statement stressed that despite the provocations, 
Nigerian troops had remained calm, as war is not the only means 
of resolving disputes. While Nigeria continues to pursue a 
peaceful approach, it said that Nigerian troops will continue to 
keep to orders to protect the lives and property of Nigerians 
residing in the disputed area. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

