  Fighting is now taking place in Bugesera region in southern 
Rwanda, which is very close to the border with northern Burundi. 
  In Kigali itself the RPF controls the northern part of the 
town [words indistinct] southern part of the town. 
  The liberation of the country is thus already a reality for 
the people. However, each Rwandan is still expected to 
contribute to that liberation by supporting the RPF combatants, 
and all those acting to help rid the country of the current 
dictatorship. 

