<F P=106> [From the "African news"] </F>
  [Text] Voting scheduled for today in the three 
parliamentary by-elections in Togo has been postponed. An 
official announcement gave no reason for the postponement but 
said the elections would be held as soon as circumstances 
permitted. Reports say the technical preparations have not been 
completed, and there has been no campaigning. Opposition 
parties were declared the winners in the three constituencies in 
the elections last February, but the Supreme Court has ordered a 
revote. 

