  [Text] Mmabatho public servants have decided on an 
indefinite go-slow strike. The decision was taken in defiance 
of a call by the North-West premier, Mr. Popo Molefe, for them 
to act in a professional manner. The approximately 500 civil 
servants also expressed their anger at Mr. Molefe for slamming 
their demands for salary parity with white officials. A senior 
official said that before the elections Mr. Molefe had termed 
the demand as their right, now he referred to it as stupid. 

