<H3> <TI>   Western Cape Premier Announces Official Languages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Western Cape Premier Announces Official Languages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1405123794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1405123794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The official languages of the western Cape region 
will be English, Afrikaans, and Xhosa. This was announced by 
provincial premier, Hernus Kriel, at a reception at the former 
administrator's residence in Cape Town. He said that the 
Western Cape Provincial Assembly would begin its work on the 
first of August. 

</TEXT>

