<H3> <TI>   Radio Pretoria Divided Over Whether To Resume Broadcasts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Pretoria Divided Over Whether To Resume Broadcasts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1405165594 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 
1600 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1405165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>
<F P=105>  Afrikaans </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A fight broke out this morning between two factions 
of Radio Pretoria supporters over the resumption of broadcasts. 
The station has been closed after a prohibition on further 
transmissions by the Supreme Court. Rev. Mossie van den Berg, 
chairman of the Executive Committee, had recommended that the 
station should wait on a final decision from the Independent 
Broadcasting Authority regarding the issue of a license to the 
station. 
  According to the station's spokesperson, Commandant Piet le 
Roux, Rev. van der Berg this morning addressed supporters, and 
Mr. Manie Maritz, a prominent right-winger, asked to express his 
views. He asked that a new Executive Committee be elected. A 
fight broke out. According to Commandant le Roux, the conflict 
began when Rev. van der Berg instructed that the station be 
closed down. The opposing faction is now threatening to resume 
transmissions next week. 

</TEXT>

