<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   SAA To Terminate Weekly Flights to Lisbon in Sept </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SAA To Terminate Weekly Flights to Lisbon in Sept </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1405123994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1405123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] South African Airways [SAA] is to terminate its 
weekly service to Lisbon as part of a program to rationalize its 
route network. SAA said in a statement that the Lisbon service 
had been cut as it was not economically viable. The last flight 
to the Portuguese capital will be in September. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

