<F P=102>   MB1805075094 Johannesburg SAPA in English 2346 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1805075094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Umtata May 17 SAPA -- The chief of the South African 
Air Force, Lt-Gen James Kriel, assured members of the former 
Transkei Defence Force on Tuesday that their jobs would be safe 
in the new South African National Defence Force. Speaking after 
meeting with members of the former Transkei Defence Force Gen 
Kriel said the integration of the airwings of the former 
homeland armies would not pose a problem. "People should not 
fear that they will lose their jobs and benefits because of this 
new setup. There will be no discrimination on the colour of the 
skin", Gen Kriel said. 
  The Umtata airwing will close at the end of May and its 
aircraft will be transferred to Bloemfontein in the Orange Free 
State. 

