<H3> <TI>   Radio Reports Vote Counting Under Way </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Reports Vote Counting Under Way </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1805110694 Blantyre Malawi Broadcasting Corporation 
Network in English 0500 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1805110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Blantyre Malawi Broadcasting Corporation 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Counting of votes in the country's first multiparty 
parliamentary and presidential elections continues. MBC 
correspondents around the country said so far indications are 
that the Alliance for Democracy, AFORD, is doing very well in 
the northern region. The Malawi Congress Party, MCP, is gaining 
ground in the central Region and the United Democratic Front, 
UDF, is making steady progress in the southern region. 

</TEXT>

