<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Malawi </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ntaba Denies Presence of Young Pioneers in Mozambique </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ntaba Denies Presence of Young Pioneers in Mozambique </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1705123394 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0800 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1705123394 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Malawian Foreign Minister Dr. Hetherwick Ntaba says 
there is no proof that the Mozambique National Resistance is 
harboring Malawi Young Pioneers. Dr. Ntaba added that his 
government has always been willing to repatriate the probable 
elements of the military wing of President Banda's party, but 
that has not yet happened. The Malawian foreign minister was 
speaking to a group of Southern African Development Community 
journalists at the end of the parliamentary session which 
adopted Malawi's new constitution. Dr. Ntaba noted that all 
members of the armed unit were demobilized soon after the 
referendum held in 1993 following complaints by opposition 
parties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

