<H3> <TI>   Minister Orders Shop Alongs Angolan Border Closed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Orders Shop Alongs Angolan Border Closed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1805091794 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation 
Network in English 1800 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1805091794 </F>
<F P=104>  Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Northwestern Province Deputy Minister Reverend Amos 
Chisipawa has directed police in Mililunga to close two shops 
opened on the Angolan border by a foreign investor. Addressing 
public workers at Mililunga Secondary School, Rev. Chipawa said 
that police in the area should not allow foreign investors to 
establish shops in the border area. He emphasized that 
investors interested in retail should establish shops at the 
Boma [traditional authority] and not border areas because the 
peace of the nation could be compromised. The minister called on 
Zambians to be security conscious and report suspicions 
characters to authorities. 

</TEXT>

