<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe, worried that 
continued world attention on South Africa may marginalize 
neighboring Zimbabwe, will try to persuade British investors in 
London on Thursday to bolster his country's economy. 
  Zimbabwean leaders have been touring the world in the past 
few months on an investment campaign aimed at boosting an 
economy burdened by rising unemployment. The Zimbabwean 
president will concentrate in London on his country's track 
record of peace in contrast to continued violence in South 
Africa. Announcements on tax relief and amendments to the 
controversial program are also expected. 

