<H3> <TI>   Vice President Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vice President Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1505175094 Khartoum SUNA in English 0950 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA1505175094 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Juba, 15 May (SUNA) -- The convention of Juba 
peace gathering affirms the southerners' extreme desire for 
peace, said Vice President Major General George Kongor. 
  Addressing the opening session of the gathering, Kongor said 
that the gathering is a message unanimously reached by the 
internal front to condemn the acts of those who back the 
continuation of the war in the south. The revolution, he said, 
is keen to achieve the Sudanese peoples' full desire for a 
comprehensive peace and stability in southern Sudan. All the 
Sudanese people reject the continuation of the 14-year war, he 
added. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

